  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6582.95 sitting below the 6591 flip point in PIN regime, dealers are currently buying the dip as they're long gamma and providing stabilizing flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6600 (48.8B) will create heavy dealer selling pressure on any rally attempt, while the negative gamma pocket at 6560 (-9.0B) should provide buying support if we drift lower. The recent GEX surge combined with the tight 6580-6600 range packed with positive gamma walls suggests dealers will aggressively fade any directional moves, keeping price action compressed.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy, range-bound trading between 6560-6600 with dealers capping upside moves.",
